<para> Why does the professor say this: <mediaExhibit frameType="mp3" mediaRef="toeflPrac10234_02.mp3"/></para>
</question-stem>
<answer-choice-set>
<answer-choice correct="yes"> To emphasize that all humans are born with an
ability to learn language</answer-choice>
<answer-choice> To indicate that genetic background plays a role in determining
how well people acquire languages</answer-choice>
<answer-choice> To correct a commonly held misperception about language acquisition</answer-choice>
<answer-choice> To assure her audience that all children can be taught to
read and write</answer-choice>
</answer-choice-set>
<explanation interaction="true">
<para> The professor states that the language skill is innate, which means
that all humans are born with it, so (A) is correct. This does not determine
how well the language will be acquired, so (B) does not relate to her statement.
She does not state that this contradicts a common misperception (C), and she
is talking about spoken language, not reading and writing, so (D) is incorrect.</para>
</explanation>
